comment.narrative:
1.	Gender-sensitive NIAS impact monitoring public opinion survey conducted
2.	The “e-Integrity” informational system updated and its interoperability with other anticorruption e-tools and modules ensured.
3.	Corruption proofing expertise software upgraded by including a module for draft normative acts and by improving the statistical monitoring module;
4.	At least 3 public awareness campaigns on anticorruption and integrity conducted;
5.	Capacity of at least 70 % of NIAS focal points on the results-based implementation of NIAS at the central and local level (from at least 70% of districts) strengthened;
6.	Capacities of 20 CSO’s to produce shadow monitoring reports on the implementation of the NIAS and sector/local plans strengthened;
7.	Summer school for 20 anticorruption volunteers organized and at least 5 anticorruption volunteers’ initiatives supported.

1.	Achieved. Gender-sensitive NIAS impact monitoring public opinion survey conducted. 
2.	Achieved. The “e-Integrity” informational system updated and its interoperability with other anticorruption e-tools and modules ensured. The system will be launched and fully operational by February 2020.
3.	Achieved. Corruption proofing expertise software upgraded by including a module for draft normative acts and by improving the statistical monitoring module;
4.	Exceeded. 4 complex public awareness campaigns on anticorruption and integrity conducted: (1) whistleblowing and the protection of whistleblowers, (2) integrity standards in the private sector, (3)educating integrity values among youth, (4) Anticorruption Day in your Town. 4 video spots, one rap song and 15 video stories designed and distributed. About 1,000,000 men and women and girls and boys were reached by the awareness campaigns on social media, TV and through training activities and promo materials;
5.	Exceeded. Capacity of at 95 % of NIAS focal points on the results-based implementation of NIAS at the central and local level (from 30 out of 32 districts (94%) strengthened. A total of 129 NIAS focal points, including 58 at local level trained and capacitated on M&E and results based reporting on NIAS;
6.	Exceeded. Capacities of 44 representatives from 27 NGOs in shadow monitoring of the implementation of NIAS local and sector level anticorruption action plans strengthened. 9 small grants awarded to 8 NGOs for shadow monitoring of 10 local and 5 sectorial anticorruption action plans within a grants competition.
7.	Exceeded. Summer school for 30 anticorruption volunteers organized and 6 anticorruption volunteers’ initiatives supported (flashmobs for corruption free education, short videos promoting integrity messages, anticorruption debates).
